headline: Ahead of Holidays, Target Launches First-of-its-Kind Accessible Self-Checkout Nationwide
summary: Target Corporation (NYSE: TGT) today announced the launch of a first-of-its-kind accessible self-checkout experience, designed with and for guests with disabilities, including those who are blind or have low vision. Beginning this holiday season and continuing into early 2026, the solution will roll out to self-checkout stations across Target stores nationwide, as part of Target's ongoing checkout improvements. headline: MAC.BID Makes Georgia Debut with Online Auction, Bin Store Opening in Macon
summary: Online retail liquidation company, MAC.BID, announced today the opening of a new location in Macon, Georgia, on October 4, continuing the company's rapid national growth. The Pennsylvania-based company now operates nearly 30 locations across the country, with recent expansion underway in Arizona, Colorado, Nevada, North Carolina, Ohio, Pennsylvania, South Carolina, Tennessee, and Texas.
